{"title_page": "Herv\u00e9 Pinoteau", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}}\nBaron '''Herv\u00e9 Pinoteau''' (born 19 July 1927) is a French historian and royalist [[Wiktionary:apologist|apologist]].<ref>{{Cite web|author=Pinoteau, Herv\u00e9 |date=27 August 2004 |title=Le Prince que j'ai servi |language=French |publisher=Vexilla Regis Prodeunt |url=http://vexilla-regis.com/textevr/Princequejaiservi.htm |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SnBQtOpl?url=http://vexilla-regis.com/textevr/Princequejaiservi.htm |archivedate=23 September 2014 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He is the author of more than 900 articles and 22 books primarily on history and heraldry.<ref name=\"ASM\">{{Cite web|title=Pinoteau Herv\u00e9, baron|publisher=l'Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences Morales, des Lettres et des Arts de Versailles et d'\u00cele-de-France|language=French|url=http://www.academiedeversailles.com/detail.php?categorie_id=1&scategorie_id=28&contact_id=75|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Sn9duIbo?url=http://www.academiedeversailles.com/detail.php?categorie_id=1&scategorie_id=28&contact_id=75|archivedate=23 September 2014|url-status=dead|access-date=23 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nPinoteau was born in Paris. From 1950 to 1951, he served in the French army as a lieutenant.<ref name=\"ASM\" /> He served as the private secretary of the late [[Alfonso, Duke of Anjou and C\u00e1diz|Prince Alfonso, Duke of Anjou]], for 26 years.<ref>{{Cite news |author=Hanne, Isabelle |date=2 January 2009 |title=SAR \u00bb sur le passeport : petits privil\u00e8ges pour princes de sang |newspaper=Le Nouvel Observateur Rue89 |url=http://rue89.nouvelobs.com/explicateur/2009/01/02/sar-sur-le-passeport-petits-privileges-pour-princes-de-sang |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SnJ5subf?url=http://rue89.nouvelobs.com/explicateur/2009/01/02/sar-sur-le-passeport-petits-privileges-pour-princes-de-sang |archivedate=23 September 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all |access-date=23 September 2014 }}</ref>\n\nPinoteau is a member of the [[Acad\u00e9mie Internationale d'H\u00e9raldique]] (International Academy of Heraldry) of which he was general secretary from 1964 to 1988.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Historique du Bureau de l\u2019A.I.H. |year=1998 |language=French |publisher=Acad\u00e9mie Internationale d'H\u00e9raldique |url=http://aih-1949.com/histoire_4.phpF |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SnCELgd5?url=http://aih-1949.com/histoire_4.php |archivedate=23 September 2014 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He was president of the Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 nationale des Antiquaires de France in 2010.<ref name=\"ASM\" /> He was recognized as an expert in French [[heraldry]] and [[vexology]]. He was commissioned to create the coat of arms of the [[Pays de la Loire]] region of France, and to do the final design for the coat of arms of the [[Republic of Chad]].<ref name=\"ASM\" /> Pinoteau is a [[monarchist]] who believes in the restoration of the [[House of Bourbon]] to the French throne. He was the founder of the Secretariat-du Prince Alphonse, Duc de Bourbon (1962) and the Institut de la maison de Bourbon (1973). He is considered one of the innovators of the [[Legitimists|legitimist movement]] in France.\n\n==Awards==\n* Knight of the [[Legion of Honour]] (French: Ordre national de la L\u00e9gion d'honneur)\n* Commander of the [[Order of Prince Henry the Navigator]] (Portuguese: Ordem do Infante Dom Henrique)\n* Grand officer of the [[Civil Order of Alfonso X, the Wise]] (Spanish: Orden de Alfonso X el Sabio)\n* 1990 - National History Prize of the National Academy of Reims - Paillard Foundation (l\u2019Acad\u00e9mie nationale de Reims - Fondation Paillard)\n\n==Selected works==\nAmong his many publications are contributions to:\n* ''[[Encyclop\u00e6dia universalis]]'' (''Thesaurus Index''),<ref>{{Cite web|title=Herv\u00e9 Pinoteau, vice-pr\u00e9sident de l'Acad\u00e9mie internationale d'h\u00e9raldique, Auteur de:|url=http://www.universalis.fr/auteurs/herve-pinoteau/}}</ref> \n* ''Dictionnaire du Grand si\u00e8cle'' de Fran\u00e7ois Bluche, \n* ''Dictionnaire du Second Empire'' de [[Jean Tulard]], \n* ''Encyclop\u00e9die de la culture fran\u00e7aise'' d\u2019\u00c9clectis, \n* ''Dictionnaire de biographie fran\u00e7aise'', and\n* ''Dictionnaire mondial des images'' de [[Laurent Gervereau]].\n\n===Books===\n\n* ''Monarchie et avenir'', Nouvelles Editions Latines, Paris 1960\n* ''L'h\u00e9raldique cap\u00e9tienne'', 1976, revised 2000\n* ''L'\u00c9tat de l'Ordre du Saint-Esprit en 1830 et la survivance des ordres du roi'', 1983\n* Herv\u00e9 Pinoteau, Fabien Gandrille, Christian Papet-Vauban, ''Etat pr\u00e9sent de la maison de Bourbon : pour servir de suite \u00e0 l'almanach royal de 1830 et \u00e0 d'autres publications officielles de la Maison'', L\u00e9opard d'or, 1986\n* ''\u00c9tudes sur les ordres de chevalerie du Roi de France'', Le l\u00e9opard d'Or, Paris 1995\n* ''Le chaos fran\u00e7ais et ses signes'', 1998\n* Herv\u00e9 Pinoteau, Jean de Vaulchier, Jacques Amable de Saulieu, Jean de Bodinat, ''Armorial de l'ANF - Association d'entraide de la Noblesse Fran\u00e7aise - Herv\u00e9 Pinoteau : H\u00e9raldique et noblesse en pr\u00e9face de l'ouvrage''\n* ''La symbolique royale fran\u00e7aise'', 2004\n* ''Saint Louis: Son entourage et la symbolique chr\u00e9tienne'', 2006\n* ''Cinq \u00e9tudes d'h\u00e9raldique et de symbolique \u00e9tatique'', L\u00e9opard d'or, 2007\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n{{-}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pinoteau, Herve}}\n[[Category:1927 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Paris]]\n[[Category:French heraldists]]\n[[Category:French historians]]\n[[Category:Chevaliers of the L\u00e9gion d'honneur]]\n[[Category:Commanders of the Order of Prince Henry]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Civil Order of Alfonso X, the Wise]]\n[[Category:French male non-fiction writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}}\nBaron '''Herv\u00e9 Pinoteau''' (born 19 July 1927) is a French historian and royalist [[Wiktionary:apologist|apologist]].<ref>{{Cite web|author=Pinoteau, Herv\u00e9 |date=27 August 2004 |title=Le Prince que j'ai servi |language=French |publisher=Vexilla Regis Prodeunt |url=http://vexilla-regis.com/textevr/Princequejaiservi.htm |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SnBQtOpl?url=http://vexilla-regis.com/textevr/Princequejaiservi.htm |archivedate=23 September 2014 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He is the author of more than 900 articles and 22 books primarily on history and heraldry.<ref name=\"ASM\">{{Cite web|title=Pinoteau Herv\u00e9, baron|publisher=l'Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences Morales, des Lettres et des Arts de Versailles et d'\u00cele-de-France|language=French|url=http://www.academiedeversailles.com/detail.php?categorie_id=1&scategorie_id=28&contact_id=75|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Sn9duIbo?url=http://www.academiedeversailles.com/detail.php?categorie_id=1&scategorie_id=28&contact_id=75|archivedate=23 September 2014|url-status=dead|access-date=23 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nPinoteau was born in Paris. From 1950 to 1951, he served in the French army as a lieutenant.<ref name=\"ASM\" /> He served as the private secretary of the late [[Alfonso, Duke of Anjou and C\u00e1diz|Prince Alfonso, Duke of Anjou]], for 26 years.<ref>{{Cite news |author=Hanne, Isabelle |date=2 January 2009 |title=SAR \u00bb sur le passeport : petits privil\u00e8ges pour princes de sang |newspaper=Le Nouvel Observateur Rue89 |url=http://rue89.nouvelobs.com/explicateur/2009/01/02/sar-sur-le-passeport-petits-privileges-pour-princes-de-sang |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SnJ5subf?url=http://rue89.nouvelobs.com/explicateur/2009/01/02/sar-sur-le-passeport-petits-privileges-pour-princes-de-sang |archivedate=23 September 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all |access-date=23 September 2014 }}</ref>\n\nPinoteau is a member of the [[Acad\u00e9mie Internationale d'H\u00e9raldiqu